# Caddy site block for the Kausapp admin (appended to /etc/caddy/Caddyfile on the droplet).
#
# admin.kausapp.com gets a REAL Let's Encrypt cert via the Cloudflare DNS-01 challenge
# (the domain points to a private Tailscale IP, so HTTP/TLS-ALPN challenges can't work).
# It then REDIRECTS to the tailnet-only admin service on the droplet's Tailscale IP.
#
# Direct reverse_proxy + a remote_ip filter was tried first but wouldn't load on the
# user's device; a plain redirect to the working IP:port is reliable. The redirect
# target (100.99.99.75:8080) is a private tailnet address, so it's only reachable from
# the tailnet anyway.

admin.kausapp.com {
    tls {
        dns cloudflare {env.CF_API_TOKEN}
    }
    redir http://100.99.99.75:8080{uri}
}
